{
  "stem": "4189.1",
  "chunk_idx": 1,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And then, of course, in November-- November 9, 1938, that was the Kristallnacht.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "[CLEARS THROAT] All of the Jewish businesses were destroyed.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Our store was vandalized and all the windows were open, some of the furnitures were carried away and all the synagogues were put on fire.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "At that time, I was-- I was only 14 years old, and my mother was very worried about her sister, Frances.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "See, her sister also had a furniture store, and she had two little children at that time.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They were very small.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And we knew that where she lived there was a synagogue in the back of the building.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "There was another building, and that building was a synagogue, and we were trying to get in touch with her.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "We couldn't.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Somehow, we couldn't get in touch with her.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "There was nobody home.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "So finally, the next morning my mother said that I should take my bicycle and go and see what had happened to her.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "So I did this, and as they went out, I went through the neighborhood there.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And I saw, of course, all the Jewish shops were all broken into, all the glass was laying in the street.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "As a matter of fact, on our street where our store was, there was a synagogue which was on a first floor of another building.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And that synagogue, they could not burn it because there were people living in the building.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "So what they did, they throw all the Torah scrolls out in the street.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "Everything was lay in the street, the benches, the books.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And it was totally destroyed.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "But I just took my bicycle, and I kept on going to my aunt's house, which is about 10 minutes away.",
      "word_count": 21
    }
  ],
